==Old English==

===Etymology===
Germanic ''*ôþ-'', from Indo-European ''*āt'' ‘[[race]], [[people]]’.
Germanic cognates include Old Frisian ''ēþel'', Old Saxon [[óðil]], Old High German [[uodil]], Old Norse [[óðal]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'e:ðel/

===Noun===
'''ēþel''' ''m'' (''pl'' '''ēþlas''')
# ancestral land, [[home]], [[territory]]
#:''Ic ealne geondhwearf eðel Gotena'': I travelled through all the country of the Goths.
# the rune ᛟ

